The paper deals with explaining black box models, which is a common problem in the field of artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of machine learning (ML) models, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The need for legal and regulatory frameworks around AI and ML systems suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the potential applications of the proposed method in explanation-critical scenarios, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper involves the development of a method for generating explanations, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering).
